<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Buck</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-30"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 358.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At the instance of the Secretary of the
                            Navy, as expressed in his letter of the 20th instant, I have now to
                            instruct you to express to the Government of Japan the cordial
                            appreciation and thanks of this Government for the unusual courtesy
                            shown by Japanese officials and subjects to the squadron of United
                            States ships which was present during the unveiling of the Perry
                            monument on the 14th instant.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>